House Resolution 571
By: Representatives Rhodes of the 124th and Jackson of the 128th
A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life and memory of Elizabeth Cail Newsome Hammons; and for other
2 purposes.
3 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia mourns the loss of one of its most distinguished citizens
4 with the passing of Elizabeth Cail Newsome Hammons on August 29, 2024; and
5 WHEREAS, Elizabeth Cail Newsome Hammons was born on September 28, 1978, in
6 Warrenton, Georgia, a beloved daughter of James and Susan McManus Newsome; and
7 WHEREAS, a graduate of Georgia College and State University, she dedicated her career
8 to the preservation and revitalization of rural communities across Georgia, serving the City
9 of Greensboro for over 18 years as main street manager and later as community development
10 director; and
11 WHEREAS, during her tenure, she oversaw transformative projects such as the
12 redevelopment of a multipurpose performing arts center, the rehabilitation of an old cotton
13 warehouse, the installation of gateway signage, and vital park improvements; and
