14 WHEREAS, she was instrumental in securing millions of dollars in grant funding for
15 Greensboro through Community Development Block Grants, park grants, emergency
16 response grants, and additional funding programs as well as overseeing owner-occupied
17 home rehabilitations through the CHIP program; and
18 WHEREAS, she further managed Greensboro's Historic Preservation Committee, oversaw
19 the city's comprehensive and five-year plans, secured Downtown Development Revolving
20 Loan Funds and Georgia Cities funding for small businesses, and led Greensboro's
21 participation in the Georgia Initiative for Community Housing; and
22 WHEREAS, she was united in love and marriage to her husband, Matt, and the two were
23 blessed with a remarkable son, Lee, whom she considered her proudest achievement; and
24 WHEREAS, a compassionate and generous woman, Elizabeth Cail Newsome Hammons will
25 long be remembered for her love of family, friendship, and community and will be missed
26 by all who had the great fortune of knowing her.
27 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
28 the members of this body join in honoring the life and memory of Elizabeth Cail Newsome
29 Hammons and express their deepest and most sincere regret at her passing.
30 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
31 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the
32 family of Elizabeth Cail Newsome Hammons.
